  protein: 39 g
  fiber: 12 g
  sodium: 1110 mg
servings: 2
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Dice @Yukon Gold potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch pieces. Peel @garlic{1%clove}. Cut @broccoli{8%ounce} florets into bite-size pieces if necessary. Halve, core, and dice @apple{1}(halved, cored, and diced into ¼-inch pieces). Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}(trimmed and thinly sliced, whites separated from greens). Zest and quarter @lemon{1}(zested and quartered).

== Mashed Potatoes ==

Place potatoes and whole garlic in a #medium pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Reserve ½ cup potato cooking liquid, then drain and return potatoes and garlic to pot.

Keep covered off heat until ready to mash.

== Broccoli ==

Toss broccoli on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tablespoon}, @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

== Chicken ==

While broccoli roasts, pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}. Season lightly with salt and pepper, then rub all over with @McCormick Grill Mates Brown Sugar Bourbon Seasoning{10.8%g}.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium heat. Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{5-7%minutes} per side.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

== Apple Pan Sauce ==

Heat @butter{1%tablespoon} and a drizzle of oil in same pan over medium-high heat. Add apple and scallion whites; season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, until golden, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Stir in @chicken stock concentrate{1}, @water{1/2%cup}, and @sugar{1/2%teaspoon}. Cook until apple is tender and sauce has thickened, ~{5-7%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper.

In the last 2 minutes, add chicken to pan; turn a few times to coat.

== Finish ==

While sauce cooks, mash drained potatoes and garlic with @sour cream{2%tablespoon} and @butter{1%tablespoon} until smooth and creamy with a #potato masher{}, adding splashes of reserved potato cooking liquid as needed. Season with salt and pepper.

> If necessary, rewarm over low heat.

Carefully toss roasted broccoli with lemon zest.

Divide chicken, garlic mashed potatoes, and zesty broccoli between plates. Spoon remaining sauce from pan over chicken and garnish with scallion greens. Serve with lemon wedges on the side.